(328, 56, 'title_1', 'Term Insurance is best in two circumstances:'),
(329, 56, '_title_1', 'field_5cebb9ee62a8e'),
(330, 56, 'text_1', '<ol>\r\n 	<li>An individual requires the coverage for only a set period. For example: to pay off a mortgage, or replace a spouse income while the children in the home are still young.</li>\r\n 	<li>An individual has a limited budget and has a high need for insurance. Many people think that all life insurance is very unaffordable, but when you consider a term product for a relatively healthy 35-year-old male non-smoker could purchase $1,000,000 of 10-year term coverage for around $40.00 per month, it becomes much more affordable.</li>\r\n</ol>'),
